### Day 10 - Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA)

#### Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA)

- MFA adds an extra layer of security beyond passwords.
- Requires two or more forms of authentication.
- Common factors in MFA include something you know, something you have, and something you are.

### Access Governance

- Key components of access governance include access certification, segregation of duties (SoD), entitlement management, access request and approval, and access monitoring and reporting.
- Manages access to resources in an organization's IT environment.

### Customer IAM

- Customer IAM focuses on managing the identities and access rights of customers and external users.
- Key features of CIAM include user registration and onboarding, single sign-on (SSO), social login, consent management, self-service profile management, and identity verification.

### API Security

- Key aspects of API security include authentication, authorization, encryption, rate limiting, input validation and sanitization, auditing and monitoring, and secure development practices.
- Protects APIs from unauthorized access and abuse.

